HEADWORD: naid
<hw>na"id</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Naiad</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of numerous
species of small, fresh-water, chaetopod annelids of the tribe
<fam>Naidina</fam>. They belong to the <ord>Oligochaeta</ord>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

